352
00:14:38,689 --> 00:14:40,469
Whom have I the honour to address?"

353
00:14:41,910 --> 00:14:45,220
"You may address me as the Count Von Kramm,

354
00:14:45,220 --> 00:14:46,280
a Bohemian nobleman.

355
00:14:47,179 --> 00:14:49,819
I understand that this gentleman, your

356
00:14:49,819 --> 00:14:53,539
friend, is a man of honour and discretion,

357
00:14:53,540 --> 00:14:55,880
whom I may trust with a matter of the most

358
00:14:55,879 --> 00:14:56,999
extreme importance.

359
00:14:57,959 --> 00:15:01,259
If not, I should much prefer to communicate

360
00:15:01,259 --> 00:15:02,619
with you alone."

361
00:15:02,619 --> 00:15:05,829
I rose to go, but Holmes caught me by the

362
00:15:05,829 --> 00:15:08,989
wrist and pushed me back into my chair.

363
00:15:08,990 --> 00:15:12,070
"It is both, or none," said he.

364
00:15:12,069 --> 00:15:14,369
"You may say before this gentleman anything

365
00:15:14,369 --> 00:15:16,679
which you may say to me."

366
00:15:16,679 --> 00:15:18,729
The Count shrugged his broad shoulders.

367
00:15:18,730 --> 00:15:23,260
"Then I must begin," said he, "by binding

368
00:15:23,259 --> 00:15:27,329
