00:20:47,230 --> 00:20:49,000
"Your Majesty must pay.

492
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:50,970
It must be bought."

493
00:20:50,970 --> 00:20:53,120
"She will not sell."

494
00:20:53,120 --> 00:20:54,880
"Stolen, then."

495
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:57,520
"Five attempts have been made.

496
00:20:57,519 --> 00:20:59,929
Twice burglars in my pay ransacked her

497
00:20:59,929 --> 00:21:01,079
house.

498
00:21:01,080 --> 00:21:03,230
Once we diverted her luggage when she

499
00:21:03,230 --> 00:21:04,400
travelled.

500
00:21:04,399 --> 00:21:06,389
Twice she has been waylaid.

501
00:21:06,389 --> 00:21:08,889
There has been no result."

502
00:21:08,889 --> 00:21:09,889
"No sign of it?"

503
00:21:09,889 --> 00:21:14,059
"Absolutely none."

504
00:21:14,059 --> 00:21:14,529
Holmes laughed.

505
00:21:15,549 --> 00:21:18,319
"It is quite a pretty little problem," said

506
00:21:18,320 --> 00:21:18,570
he.

507
00:21:18,320 --> 00:21:23,840
"But a very serious one to me," returned

508
00:21:23,840 --> 00:21:26,040
the King reproachfully.

509
00:21:26,039 --> 00:21:27,769
"Very, indeed.

510
00:21:27,769 --> 00:21:30,509
And what does she propose to do with the

511
00:21:30,510 --> 00:21:31,680
photograph?"

