00:22:47,929 --> 00:22:50,519
"That is very fortunate, as I have one or

546
00:22:50,519 --> 00:22:53,139
two matters of importance to look into just

547
00:22:53,139 --> 00:22:54,549
at present.

548
00:22:54,549 --> 00:22:56,509
Your Majesty will, of course, stay in

549
00:22:56,510 --> 00:22:57,580
London for the present?"

550
00:22:57,580 --> 00:23:00,400
"Certainly.

551
00:23:00,399 --> 00:23:02,459
You will find me at the Langham under the

552
00:23:02,460 --> 00:23:04,830
name of the Count Von Kramm."

553
00:23:04,830 --> 00:23:07,700
"Then I shall drop you a line to let you

554
00:23:07,700 --> 00:23:10,220
know how we progress."

555
00:23:10,220 --> 00:23:11,600
"Pray do so.

556
00:23:11,600 --> 00:23:14,730
I shall be all anxiety."

557
00:23:14,730 --> 00:23:17,910
"Then, as to money?"

558
00:23:17,909 --> 00:23:20,119
"You have carte blanche."

559
00:23:20,120 --> 00:23:21,390
"Absolutely?"

560
00:23:21,389 --> 00:23:24,399
"I tell you that I would give one of the

561
00:23:24,399 --> 00:23:27,729
provinces of my kingdom to have that

562
00:23:27,730 --> 00:23:28,400
photograph."

563
00:23:28,399 --> 00:23:29,889
"And for present expenses?"

564
00:23:30,909 --> 00:23:33,449
The King took a heavy chamois leather bag

565
00:23:33,450 --> 00:23:35,160
from under his cloak and laid it on the

566
00:23:35,159 --> 00:23:35,509
table.

567
00:23:35,510 --> 00:23:39,600
"There are three hundred pounds in gold and

568
00:23:39,600 --> 00:23:42,400
seven hundred in notes," he said.

569
00:23:42,399 --> 00:23:44,639
Holmes scribbled a receipt upon a sheet of

570
00:23:44,639 --> 00:23:48,099
his note-book and handed it to him.

571
00:23:48,100 --> 00:23:51,760
"And Mademoiselle's address?" he asked.

572
00:23:51,759 --> 00:23:55,349
"Is Briony Lodge, Serpentine Avenue, St.

573
00:23:55,350 --> 00:23:57,620
John's Wood."

574
00:23:57,620 --> 00:23:59,610
Holmes took a note of it.

575
00:23:59,610 --> 00:24:02,640
"One other question," said he.

576
00:24:02,639 --> 00:24:05,599
"Was the photograph a cabinet?"

577
00:24:05,600 --> 00:24:07,510
"It was."

578
00:24:07,509 --> 00:24:10,019
"Then, good-night, your Majesty, and I

579
00:24:10,019 --> 00:24:12,069
trust that we shall soon have some good

580
00:24:12,070 --> 00:24:12,790
news for you.

581
00:24:13,590 --> 00:24:16,460
And good-night, Watson," he added, as the

582
00:24:16,460 --> 00:24:18,600
wheels of the royal brougham rolled down

583
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:19,020
the street.

584
00:24:19,929 --> 00:24:22,019
"If you will be good enough to call to-

585
00:24:22,019 --> 00:24:24,639
morrow afternoon at three o'clock I should

586
00:24:24,639 --> 00:24:26,889
like to chat this little matter over with

587
00:24:26,889 --> 00:24:27,139
you."

588
00:24:27,009 --> 00:24:32,199
II.

589
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:35,140
At three o'clock precisely I was at Baker

590
00:24:35,139 --> 00:24:37,169
Street, but Holmes had not yet returned.

591
00:24:38,279 --> 00:24:40,559
The landlady informed me that he had left

592
00:24:40,559 --> 00:24:42,519
the house shortly after eight o'clock in

593
00:24:42,519 --> 00:24:43,639
the morning.

594
00:24:43,639 --> 00:24:46,349
I sat down beside the fire, however, with

595
00:24:46,350 --> 00:24:48,780
the intention of awaiting him, however long

596
00:24:48,779 --> 00:24:49,299
he might be.

597
00:24:49,299 --> 00:24:52,329
I was already deeply interested in his

598
00:24:52,330 --> 00:24:54,980
inquiry, for, though it was surrounded by

599
00:24:54,980 --> 00:24:57,200
none of the grim and strange features which

600
00:24:57,200 --> 00:24:59,890
were associated with the two crimes which I

601
00:24:59,889 --> 00:25:03,259
have already recorded, still, the nature of

602
00:25:03,259 --> 00:25:05,849
the case and the exalted station of his

603
00:25:05,850 --> 00:25:07,970
client gave it a character of its own.

604
00:25:08,850 --> 00:25:11,360
Indeed, apart from the nature of the

605
00:25:11,360 --> 00:25:14,360
investigation which my friend had on hand,

606
00:25:14,360 --> 00:25:16,770
there was something in his masterly grasp

607
00:25:16,769 --> 00:25:20,559
of a situation, and his keen, incisive

608
00:25:20,559 --> 00:25:22,589
reasoning, which made it a pleasure to me

609
00:25:22,590 --> 00:25:25,490
to study his system of work, and to follow

610
00:25:25,490 --> 00:25:27,970
the quick, subtle methods by which he

611
00:25:27,970 --> 00:25:30,690
disentangled the most inextricable

612
00:25:30,690 --> 00:25:30,940
mysteries.

613
00:25:31,769 --> 00:25:33,949
So accustomed was I to his invariable

614
00:25:33,950 --> 00:25:36,660
success that the very possibility of his

615
00:25:36,659 --> 00:25:40,389
failing had ceased to enter into my head.

616
00:25:40,389 --> 00:25:42,669
It was close upon four before the door

617
00:25:42,669 --> 00:25:45,679
opened, and a drunken-looking groom, ill-

618
00:25:45,679 --> 00:25:48,679
kempt and side-whiskered, with an inflamed

619
00:25:48,679 --> 00:25:51,489
face and disreputable clothes, walked into

620
00:25:51,490 --> 00:25:53,010
the room.

621
00:25:53,009 --> 00:25:55,989
Accustomed as I was to my friend's amazing

622
00:25:55,990 --> 00:25:59,040
powers in the use of disguises, I had to

623
00:25:59,039 --> 00:26:01,559
look three times before I was certain that

624
00:26:01,559 --> 00:26:02,599
it was indeed he.

625
00:26:03,659 --> 00:26:05,999
With a nod he vanished into the bedroom,

626
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:08,370
whence he emerged in five minutes tweed-

627
00:26:08,370 --> 00:26:10,590
suited and respectable, as of old.

628
00:26:11,700 --> 00:26:13,550
Putting his hands into his pockets, he

629
00:26:13,549 --> 00:26:15,959
stretched out his legs in front of the fire

630
00:26:15,960 --> 00:26:18,190
and laughed heartily for some minutes.

631
00:26:19,220 --> 00:26:22,550
"Well, really!" he cried, and then he

632
00:26:22,549 --> 00:26:24,529
choked and laughed again until he was

633
00:26:24,529 --> 00:26:27,699
obliged to lie back, limp and helpless, in

634
00:26:27,700 --> 00:26:29,390
the chair.

635
00:26:29,389 --> 00:26:29,779
"What is it?"

636
00:26:29,779 --> 00:26:33,299
"It's quite too funny.

637
00:26:33,299 --> 00:26:35,769
I am sure you could never guess how I

638
00:26:35,769 --> 00:26:38,429
employed my morning, or what I ended by

639
00:26:38,429 --> 00:26:39,989
doing."

640
00:26:39,990 --> 00:26:41,920
"I can't imagine.

641
00:26:41,919 --> 00:26:44,339
I suppose that you have been watching the

642
00:26:44,340 --> 00:26:47,570
habits, and perhaps the house, of Miss

643
00:26:47,570 --> 00:26:49,310
Irene Adler."

644
00:26:49,309 --> 00:26:51,239
"Quite so; but the sequel was rather

645
00:26:51,240 --> 00:26:52,660
unusual.

646
00:26:52,659 --> 00:26:54,699
I will tell you, however.

647
00:26:54,700 --> 00:26:56,780
I left the house a little after eight

648
00:26:56,779 --> 00:26:58,719
o'clock this morning in the character of a

649
00:26:58,720 --> 00:26:59,880
groom out of work.

650
00:27:00,740 --> 00:27:02,540
There is a wonderful sympathy and

651
00:27:02,539 --> 00:27:05,159
freemasonry among horsey men.

652
00:27:05,159 --> 00:27:07,779
Be one of them, and you will know all that

653
00:27:07,779 --> 00:27:09,589
there is to know.

654
00:27:09,590 --> 00:27:12,230
I soon found Briony Lodge.

655
00:27:12,230 --> 00:27:14,840
It is a bijou villa, with a garden at the

656
00:27:14,840 --> 00:27:17,200
back, but built out in front right up to

657
00:27:17,200 --> 00:27:19,300
the road, two stories.

658
00:27:19,299 --> 00:27:20,409
Chubb lock to the door.

659
00:27:21,210 --> 00:27:23,580
Large sitting-room on the right side, well

660
00:27:23,580 --> 00:27:26,510
furnished, with long windows almost to the

661
00:27:26,509 --> 00:27:29,439
floor, and those preposterous English

662
00:27:29,440 --> 00:27:31,820
window fasteners which a child could open.

663
00:27:32,710 --> 00:27:35,060
Behind there was nothing remarkable, save

664
00:27:35,059 --> 00:27:36,789
that the passage window could be reached

665
00:27:36,789 --> 00:27:38,199
from the top of the coach-house.

666
00:27:39,139 --> 00:27:41,719
I walked round it and examined it closely

667
00:27:41,720 --> 00:27:44,060
from every point of view, but without

668
00:27:44,059 --> 00:27:47,289
noting anything else of interest.

669
00:27:47,289 --> 00:27:50,229
"I then lounged down the street and found,

670
00:27:50,230 --> 00:27:53,240
as I expected, that there was a mews in a

671
00:27:53,240 --> 00:27:55,470
lane which runs down by one wall of the

672
00:27:55,470 --> 00:27:55,760
garden.

